Foot & mouth disease [FMD] - Mongolia
-----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 16 Oct 2015 from Dr Bolortuya Purevsuren, OIE delegate, Veterinary and Animal Breeding Agency, Ministry for Industry and Agriculture, Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 2 Oct 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 15 Oct 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 3 Jun 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: food and mouth disease virus
Serotype: Pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Toshin, 3 Bag, Altai soum, Bayan-Ulgii
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Oct 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 285 / 18 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep / 1588 / 62 / 0 / 0 / 2
Goats / 965 / 10 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent]:
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 6.32 / 0 / 0 / 0
Goats / 3.90 / 0 / 0 / 0.13
Sheep / 1.04 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population **Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, screening, disinfection/disinfestations, quarantine, zoning; no vaccination, no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
From the State Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / Non-structural protein ELISA / 15 Oct 2015 / Positive
Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 15 Oct 2015 / Positive
Sheep / Non- structural protein ELISA / 16 Oct 2015 / Positive
Sheep / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 16 Oct 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[From February to May 2015, Mongolia reported 5 outbreaks of FMD, serotype O. These outbreaks were located in the Khovd (4 outbreaks) and Sukhbaatar (1 outbreak) provinces, which are in the western and eastern parts of the country, respectively. See final report and map for this event at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000018097_20150803_181045.pdf.

According to information published by the Pirbright World Reference Laboratory for Foot-and-Mouth Disease, on April 2015, FMD serotype O, topotype SEA, lineage Mya-98 was identified in Mongolia. See data at http://www.wrlfmd.org/fmd_genotyping/asia/mog.htm.

A map of the administrative divisions of Mongolia is available at http://www.ephotopix.com/mongolia_political_map.html. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3722087,1.]
